  "texts": [
    "• Using Data from Different Tasks or Modalities: Data sourced from disparate tasks or modalities can foster a more comprehensive understanding of underlying patterns and relationships, leading to enhanced model generalization.",
    "• Integration of Random Data: Introducing elements of randomness into the training dataset, thereby encouraging adaptability and resilience in the model's learning process.By scrutinizing these diverse methodologies, we aim to elucidate the multifaceted ways in which the information used for training can shape the final model.",
    "Irrelevant dataPre-training language models entail transferring linguistic knowledge collected from a data-rich task to a downstream task [5].",
    "This process serves as a foundational step in the development of robust and high-performing models.",
    "However, the ramifications of pre-training extend far beyond this initial transfer of knowledge, encompassing a myriad of nuanced effects that warrant closer examination."
